techmeme.title: Trump's acting replacements for the Copyright Office are known to be unfriendly to the tech industry and not the kind of people that AI proponents would support (Tina Nguyen/The Verge)
WhatsApp v. NSO Group: NSO kept targeting WhatsApp users even after Meta sued, it spent $59M on R&D in 2024, and its customers pay ~$3M-$30M to use Pegasus (Lorenzo Franceschi-Bicchierai/TechCrunch)
AMD and Humain partner to invest up to $10B on AI infrastructure over the next five years, including in data centers stretching from Saudi Arabia to the US (Ian King/Bloomberg)
Google says it is testing an "AI Mode" button on the Search homepage with Labs users, replacing the "I'm Feeling Lucky" button (Jennifer Elias/CNBC)
Chime files for a Nasdaq IPO under the symbol CHYM, reporting 8.6M active members at the end of March, up 23% YoY, and average revenue per active member of $251 (CNBC)
